1
00:00:32,789 --> 00:00:34,154
Cambodia.

2
00:00:35,392 --> 00:00:38,122
To many Westerners,
it seemed a paradise.

3
00:00:38,328 --> 00:00:41,491
Another world, a secret world.

4
00:00:41,798 --> 00:00:45,734
But the war in neighboring
Vietnam burst its borders...

5
00:00:45,936 --> 00:00:49,463
...and the fighting soon spread
to neutral Cambodia.

6
00:00:50,407 --> 00:00:53,604
In 1973, I went to cover
this sideshow struggle...

7
00:00:53,810 --> 00:00:56,904
...as foreign correspondent
of The New York Times.

8
00:00:57,281 --> 00:01:00,045
It was there, amidst the fighting...

9
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:03,583
...between government troops
and the Khmer Rouge guerrillas...

10
00:01:03,787 --> 00:01:07,382
...that I met my guide
and interpreter, Dith Pran...

11
00:01:07,591 --> 00:01:10,583
...a man who was to change my life...

12
00:01:10,794 --> 00:01:13,763
...in a country that I grew to love
and pity.

13
00:01:22,973 --> 00:01:25,771
So here we go
with Voice of America...

14
00:01:25,976 --> 00:01:27,967
...news for Southeast Asia.

15
00:01:28,178 --> 00:01:32,308
It's 6:45 and a partly cloudy
morning here.

16
00:01:32,516 --> 00:01:34,780
Clouds too in Washington.

17
00:01:34,985 --> 00:01:38,751
President Nixon announced he'll
address the nation on Watergate...

18
00:01:38,956 --> 00:01:40,821
...within the next few days.

19
00:01:41,024 --> 00:01:43,652
The speech will be Nixon's
first since May.

20
00:01:45,495 --> 00:01:49,522
The scandal has caused resignations
and paralyzed the White House staff.

21
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:53,328
It has also led to intense
confrontation and perhaps...

22
00:01:53,537 --> 00:01:56,404
...a constitutional crisis
with Senate investigators...

23
00:01:56,607 --> 00:01:59,235
...and a special
Watergate prosecutor.

24
00:01:59,443 --> 00:02:02,810
The speech was announced
after the Gallup Poll disclosed...

25
00:02:03,013 --> 00:02:06,881
...that Mr. Nixon's popularity
had fallen to the lowest point...

26
00:02:07,084 --> 00:02:09,882
...for an American President
in 20 years.

27
00:02:21,698 --> 00:02:24,462
A Supreme Court judge,
William O. Douglas...

28
00:02:24,668 --> 00:02:27,637
...has ruled against an appeal
by the Administration...

29
00:02:27,838 --> 00:02:29,499
...for a stay of the injunction...

30
00:02:29,706 --> 00:02:33,198
...on further U.S. Bombing
missions in Cambodia.

31
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:36,402
Congress has already ruled
these bombings illegal...

32
00:02:36,613 --> 00:02:40,879
...and they should cease in one
week's time on August the 15th.

33
00:03:02,339 --> 00:03:04,330
Let's go, Sarun!
To the hospital!

34
00:03:23,293 --> 00:03:25,420
Information. Information.

35
00:03:25,629 --> 00:03:30,566
Air Cambodia regret delays of arrival
of flight number 125...

36
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:34,396
...from Bangkok because
of bad weather.

37
00:03:55,826 --> 00:03:57,953
Mister, you want taxi?

38
00:03:58,161 --> 00:04:00,425
Mister, you want taxi?
Good taxi.

39
00:04:27,958 --> 00:04:31,018
Shut the fucking blinds, will you?

40
00:04:35,432 --> 00:04:37,093
What's all this shit?

41
00:04:40,137 --> 00:04:41,536
I'm sorry.

42
00:04:42,339 --> 00:04:45,706
I thought you were the houseboy.
I was developing some film.

43
00:04:46,209 --> 00:04:49,770
If you're gonna yell, I'll come back.
I'm not feeling good.

44
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:52,414
Don't want to yell.
I want to be in a good mood.

45
00:04:52,616 --> 00:04:55,551
The plane was late, no car.
I had to take a taxi here.

46
00:04:55,752 --> 00:04:58,118
All I want to do is work.
I got you.

47
00:05:08,098 --> 00:05:10,430
What the fuck is that on your head?

48
00:05:12,936 --> 00:05:16,428
It's a sanitary napkin.
I had it soaked in ice.

49
00:05:18,074 --> 00:05:20,736
Syd Schanberg.
Is Pran there?

50
00:05:22,612 --> 00:05:24,739
No, I just came from the airport.

51
00:05:25,682 --> 00:05:28,674
Well, if he comes in,
would you tell him I'm here?

52
00:05:29,019 --> 00:05:31,510
I'll be at the Café Central, tell him.

53
00:05:31,988 --> 00:05:32,977
Thanks a lot.

54
00:05:50,841 --> 00:05:52,035
What do you want to eat?

55
00:05:54,144 --> 00:05:55,008
Want some eggs?

56
00:05:55,212 --> 00:05:58,739
I can't. Somebody told me they faint
with fright when you cook them.

57
00:05:58,949 --> 00:06:01,179
- What do you want to eat?
- What are you having?

58
00:06:01,384 --> 00:06:02,942
I'm having a café complet.

59
00:06:03,587 --> 00:06:05,953
I'll have that. And some aspirin.

60
00:06:13,697 --> 00:06:17,258
Anything I eat has got to be
absolutely dead.

61
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:19,367
That's why I can never eat an oyster.

62
00:06:19,970 --> 00:06:22,905
I read somewhere that they put...

63
00:06:25,242 --> 00:06:28,871
...that lemon juice on them
just to stun them. You know?

64
00:06:29,079 --> 00:06:30,239
What's the difference?

65
00:06:31,715 --> 00:06:36,152
An unconscious oyster's just as
horrible as the fucker wide awake...

66
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,867
- My God! Look at this.
- Did you see that?

67
00:06:53,069 --> 00:06:54,400
What was it? A rocket?

68
00:06:54,604 --> 00:06:57,300
I don't know.
I saw a guy on a motorbike.

69
00:07:06,182 --> 00:07:07,615
I've been looking for you.

70
00:07:07,817 --> 00:07:09,375
I left a message for you.

71
00:07:09,586 --> 00:07:11,611
I didn't get it. I took a cab.

72
00:07:11,821 --> 00:07:14,756
- There is a big accident right now.
- What?

73
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:18,325
I think U.S. Drop many big bombs
on little city.

74
00:07:18,828 --> 00:07:21,854
- U.S. Bombs? You're sure?
- I think many dead.

75
00:07:22,065 --> 00:07:24,556
- Does anybody else know about it?
- Nothing at all.

76
00:07:25,535 --> 00:07:26,593
We're going.

77
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:29,361
Not possible right now, Sydney.
Too dangerous.

78
00:07:57,734 --> 00:07:59,531
Where you going, Schanberg?

79
00:08:01,104 --> 00:08:02,537
Neak Luong.

80
00:08:02,739 --> 00:08:04,001
Neak Luong's closed.

81
00:08:04,207 --> 00:08:07,973
Don't give me that, Reeves.
You got nothing to say about this.

82
00:08:08,178 --> 00:08:11,670
I got a right to go wherever I like
in this sad little country.

83
00:08:11,881 --> 00:08:16,784
That's the law. You impede me, you're
breaking the Cooper/Church Amendment!

84
00:08:16,987 --> 00:08:19,854
Well, up the Cooper/Church
Amendment's ass!

85
00:08:22,425 --> 00:08:23,585
Let's go!

86
00:08:34,537 --> 00:08:36,630
So how can I help you, Mr. Schanberg?

87
00:08:40,677 --> 00:08:45,580
I'm looking for information on why
my airplane was delayed this morning.

88
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:49,111
- Your plane was delayed?
- That's right.

89
00:08:49,319 --> 00:08:52,618
I don't know. Maybe it's
bad weather. Your flight's...

90
00:08:52,822 --> 00:08:54,881
You don't know anything about it?

91
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:56,683
No, I don't.

92
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,149
All right.

93
00:08:59,996 --> 00:09:02,487
Then I'd like you
to listen to something...

94
00:09:02,699 --> 00:09:04,724
...and then I'd like a comment.

95
00:09:05,101 --> 00:09:08,798
This morning, for reasons beyond
anybody's control...

96
00:09:09,005 --> 00:09:13,101
...I spend two hours in Bangkok
staring at a seat belt sign.

97
00:09:13,309 --> 00:09:14,867
Meanwhile, my sources tell me...

98
00:09:15,078 --> 00:09:18,878
...two Army helicopters are landing
here, just across the airfield.

99
00:09:19,449 --> 00:09:22,714
Half the ambulances in Phnom Penh
are waiting there to meet them.

100
00:09:23,119 --> 00:09:27,283
And now there's a rumor that
the U.S. Air Force dropped a bomb...

101
00:09:27,490 --> 00:09:29,390
...or several bombs, on Neak Luong.

102
00:09:29,592 --> 00:09:32,755
That's a rumor, and I'm not gonna
comment on a rumor.

103
00:09:32,962 --> 00:09:37,023
I just want to know if that's the
reason why my airplane was delayed!

104
00:09:40,904 --> 00:09:41,871
No comment.

105
00:09:42,839 --> 00:09:43,999
How many killed?

106
00:09:47,077 --> 00:09:48,374
How many wounded?

107
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:56,680
Thank you for your cooperation,
Major Reeves.

108
00:09:58,955 --> 00:10:03,187
When I scrape this story out, I will
no doubt be quoting you in full!

109
00:10:46,069 --> 00:10:47,195
I'm sorry.

110
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:49,738
This is just not good enough.

111
00:10:49,939 --> 00:10:51,930
This is a big story...

112
00:10:52,142 --> 00:10:56,374
...a major story, you understand that?
We've got to get down there!

113
00:10:56,579 --> 00:10:58,672
- I know, but...
- I don't want to hear "no"!

114
00:10:58,882 --> 00:11:00,873
I want to get down that river!

115
00:11:01,084 --> 00:11:02,813
We should be down there now!

116
00:11:15,198 --> 00:11:16,529
I'll be here.

117
00:11:19,102 --> 00:11:20,592
Good night, Sydney.

118
00:11:29,712 --> 00:11:31,475
- Messages?
- No, sir.

119
00:11:32,015 --> 00:11:33,004
No, sir.

120
00:11:35,051 --> 00:11:38,282
I'd talk, but it's been
a heavy day and I've got to go.

121
00:11:38,488 --> 00:11:40,956
Let's get together again soon, okay?

122
00:11:41,157 --> 00:11:42,522
- Bob?
- See you.

123
00:11:42,992 --> 00:11:43,959
Bob?

124
00:11:45,061 --> 00:11:47,052
Hello, Sydney. Good night, Sydney.

125
00:11:47,263 --> 00:11:50,460
- Listen, I can't talk with you.
- You can talk to me.

126
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:53,636
The embassy is jittery.
Get information from a press officer.

127
00:11:53,836 --> 00:11:56,134
Let's not start insulting each other.

128
00:11:58,441 --> 00:12:00,068
Good night, Sydney.

129
00:12:00,977 --> 00:12:02,444
All right, good night.

130
00:12:07,917 --> 00:12:09,782
You've heard of pilot error?

131
00:12:09,986 --> 00:12:11,476
Computer malfunction?

132
00:12:11,921 --> 00:12:13,821
They screwed up on the coordinates.

133
00:12:14,023 --> 00:12:17,789
A single B-52 dropped
its entire load on Neak Luong.

134
00:12:19,529 --> 00:12:22,225
There's a homing beacon
in the middle of the town.

135
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,824
- Casualties?
- You'll be briefed tomorrow.

136
00:12:26,035 --> 00:12:30,734
We estimate 55 military,
something like 35 civilians.

137
00:12:32,175 --> 00:12:33,403
How many?

138
00:12:35,812 --> 00:12:38,610
I hear it's in the hundreds.
Don't quote me on that.

139
00:12:38,815 --> 00:12:42,080
Will there be a dreadful bloodbath

140
00:12:42,285 --> 00:12:45,379
When the Khmer Rouge hit the town?

141
00:12:45,855 --> 00:12:48,551
Will there be a dreadful bloodbath...?

142
00:12:51,261 --> 00:12:53,456
Beer! We haven't had this
for four weeks.

143
00:12:53,863 --> 00:12:55,763
New York Times probably
had it flown in.

144
00:12:56,366 --> 00:12:59,767
- They keep it in their suite.
- We got a cellar. Don't you know?

145
00:12:59,969 --> 00:13:02,437
Americans take themselves so seriously.

146
00:13:02,639 --> 00:13:07,440
Don't be hard on the man. He's just
trying to get to the top of the heap.

147
00:13:07,644 --> 00:13:11,239
We'll just have to pay more to get
our telexes to the top of the heap.

148
00:13:11,447 --> 00:13:13,972
The man has just bought you a beer.
Now drink up.

149
00:13:14,183 --> 00:13:15,241
- Cheers.
- Cheers, Syd.

150
00:13:15,451 --> 00:13:17,442
- Enjoy it.
- Off to see the telex operator?

151
00:13:17,654 --> 00:13:20,054
- New York Times goes to bed early.
- Sure!

152
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:24,555
Khmer Rouge in the sunset

153
00:13:25,962 --> 00:13:28,396
The Yanks all at sea...

154
00:13:32,235 --> 00:13:34,328
- All right?
- Very possible.

155
00:13:35,505 --> 00:13:36,972
Let's go then!

156
00:13:44,981 --> 00:13:46,471
This is good work.

157
00:14:23,119 --> 00:14:24,677
- How much?
- Hundred fifty.

158
00:14:32,028 --> 00:14:33,017
One hundred!

159
00:14:39,068 --> 00:14:40,535
- All right?
- All right.

160
00:14:48,378 --> 00:14:50,073
Nice going, Pran.

161
00:15:48,838 --> 00:15:51,500
- What is he saying?
- He wants you to look at his family.

162
00:15:51,707 --> 00:15:56,144
To take a photograph and help him
because his child was wounded.

163
00:16:22,672 --> 00:16:24,765
Tell me what she's saying.

164
00:16:27,076 --> 00:16:28,566
She needs help.

165
00:16:32,515 --> 00:16:35,143
Her shop was destroyed last night.

166
00:16:36,352 --> 00:16:37,785
Her husband killed.

167
00:16:37,987 --> 00:16:39,215
How many bombs?

168
00:16:41,157 --> 00:16:42,419
She doesn't know.

169
00:16:43,526 --> 00:16:45,551
Does she know where the hospital is?

170
00:16:47,330 --> 00:16:48,661
"Just over there."

171
00:16:54,971 --> 00:16:57,201
She wants to know,
"Did someone arrest the pilot?"

172
00:16:59,842 --> 00:17:02,640
Mister, you wanna buy?
Mister, you wanna buy?

173
00:17:03,012 --> 00:17:06,243
- One dollar? You wanna buy?
- I'm out of film. I'm sorry.

174
00:17:07,416 --> 00:17:10,385
Ask her how many kids she's got
in her family.

175
00:17:11,654 --> 00:17:12,518
"Five."

176
00:17:12,989 --> 00:17:15,423
Her husband was killed already.

177
00:17:19,729 --> 00:17:20,991
What's this?

178
00:17:21,464 --> 00:17:23,227
What are these guys over here?

179
00:17:28,571 --> 00:17:31,472
In the jeep, prisoners.
Khmer Rouge prisoners.

180
00:17:54,597 --> 00:17:56,588
They kill a lot of villagers.

181
00:17:56,966 --> 00:17:59,526
She says Khmer Rouge soak rags
in gasoline...

182
00:17:59,735 --> 00:18:01,760
...and push them down
villagers' throat...

183
00:18:01,971 --> 00:18:03,962
...then set the rags alight.

184
00:18:04,206 --> 00:18:05,366
Film! No film!

185
00:18:05,575 --> 00:18:07,065
I know there's no film.

186
00:18:07,276 --> 00:18:08,402
No camera!

187
00:18:09,679 --> 00:18:10,737
No camera!

188
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:12,274
It's all right.

189
00:18:15,251 --> 00:18:16,684
Just take it easy.

190
00:18:22,658 --> 00:18:24,216
Tell them we're jour...

191
00:18:33,903 --> 00:18:35,302
Come on! Get in!

192
00:19:19,482 --> 00:19:21,109
I'm worried.

193
00:19:22,551 --> 00:19:24,951
I'm the guy who bring you over here.

194
00:19:25,721 --> 00:19:27,951
They accuse me and they arrest me.

195
00:19:28,524 --> 00:19:31,015
How can they arrest you?
You're already arrested.

196
00:19:32,528 --> 00:19:34,519
They phone Phnom Penh about me.

197
00:19:43,873 --> 00:19:45,363
I want some cigarettes.

198
00:19:47,543 --> 00:19:49,010
And I need to take a leak.

199
00:19:52,181 --> 00:19:54,172
Would you tell them I need to piss?

200
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:19,830
He said, "No piss."

201
00:20:21,677 --> 00:20:22,803
What does that mean?

202
00:20:23,345 --> 00:20:25,210
That's no piss.

203
00:20:29,719 --> 00:20:31,949
I've had enough of this bullshit.

204
00:20:32,621 --> 00:20:34,612
I got a story to get to New York!

205
00:20:39,862 --> 00:20:41,159
Don't leave me!

206
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:53,303
I won't leave you.

207
00:22:02,144 --> 00:22:04,544
They brought in the whole press corps!

208
00:22:04,747 --> 00:22:08,080
They want to sanitize the story!
Bastards!

209
00:22:18,527 --> 00:22:20,654
I am going to tell you something.

210
00:22:20,896 --> 00:22:22,557
I'm walking out of here.

211
00:22:22,765 --> 00:22:25,097
What are you gonna do?
Blow my head off?

212
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:28,359
You got a general out there,
this is an American passport...

213
00:22:28,571 --> 00:22:30,505
...and I am walking out of here!

214
00:22:33,275 --> 00:22:36,540
- He wants to get higher officer.
- Then get him! Get him!

215
00:22:44,954 --> 00:22:49,084
I'm sorry we couldn't show you the
minor bomb damage in the city itself.

216
00:22:49,291 --> 00:22:51,088
It's still a restricted area.

217
00:22:51,293 --> 00:22:53,557
Now, if you look across the river...

218
00:22:53,762 --> 00:22:56,697
...you'll see positions held by
Khmer Rouge...

219
00:22:56,899 --> 00:22:58,696
...who moved in over
the past few days.

220
00:22:58,901 --> 00:23:02,132
But the Cambodian Republican Army
is moving in on them.

221
00:23:02,338 --> 00:23:05,830
They'll have the K.R. Out
before you can say "Jack Robinson."

222
00:23:06,742 --> 00:23:08,437
Get in the chopper now!

223
00:23:08,744 --> 00:23:12,202
No, Schanberg! You came on a boat,
you go back on a boat!

224
00:23:12,414 --> 00:23:14,609
That won't stop my story!

225
00:23:17,353 --> 00:23:18,285
What is this?

226
00:23:18,487 --> 00:23:21,513
If you weren't down here,
I wouldn't be down here.

227
00:23:21,724 --> 00:23:24,625
And I don't want to be down here!
What good is it doing?

228
00:23:24,827 --> 00:23:26,658
If anybody ever reads about this...

229
00:23:26,862 --> 00:23:29,558
...you won't be able to look them
in the face!

230
00:24:09,738 --> 00:24:10,932
Good morning.

231
00:24:11,774 --> 00:24:12,763
What time is it?

232
00:24:14,743 --> 00:24:16,267
Six o'clock.

233
00:24:17,713 --> 00:24:18,611
Shit.

234
00:24:18,814 --> 00:24:20,042
Telex for you.

235
00:24:20,683 --> 00:24:22,150
You been to the telex?

236
00:24:24,553 --> 00:24:25,918
We made the front page.

237
00:24:26,121 --> 00:24:27,088
Sure.

238
00:24:29,191 --> 00:24:31,250
We must be doing something right.

239
00:24:39,234 --> 00:24:41,828
My wife is very worried.

240
00:24:42,471 --> 00:24:46,066
She thinks all foreign journalists
are going to leave Cambodia.

241
00:24:47,576 --> 00:24:49,009
Well, Pran...

242
00:24:50,212 --> 00:24:54,615
...l'd feel kind of stupid trying to
cover this war from a desk in Bangkok.

243
00:24:56,051 --> 00:24:59,145
And she said if the war
keeps going like this...

244
00:24:59,355 --> 00:25:01,516
...the future could be very bad.

245
00:25:03,392 --> 00:25:04,689
What do you think?

246
00:25:07,763 --> 00:25:09,094
I don't know.

247
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:12,965
I don't know either.

248
00:25:15,738 --> 00:25:17,706
- Is Sarun downstairs?
- Sure.

249
00:25:18,941 --> 00:25:20,340
Let's get going.

250
00:25:21,310 --> 00:25:22,277
