- Better than last year.

751
01:50:09,630 --> 01:50:12,190
Abe, meet my sister.

752
01:50:12,400 --> 01:50:14,231
I'm very happy to meet you.

753
01:50:14,435 --> 01:50:16,904
That's my dad.
Would you hold this for me?

754
01:50:18,006 --> 01:50:18,973
One second.

755
01:50:19,174 --> 01:50:22,371
I hoped you could recommend
a good school for journalism.

756
01:50:22,578 --> 01:50:25,548
I told my daughter I'd be
seeing you today.

757
01:50:25,748 --> 01:50:28,615
Just one minute, okay?
I'll be right back.

758
01:50:37,761 --> 01:50:41,561
Could I have your autograph?
I'm a great admirer of yours.

759
01:50:44,169 --> 01:50:46,865
Congratulations on your award,
it was well-deserved.

760
01:50:47,072 --> 01:50:50,337
Very impressive.
I was hoping you'd burst into song.

761
01:50:51,811 --> 01:50:54,541
- What are you doing here?
- You know what bothers me?

762
01:50:54,747 --> 01:50:55,577
What?

763
01:50:55,982 --> 01:50:58,678
It bothers me that you let Pran
stay in Cambodia...

764
01:50:58,884 --> 01:51:02,013
...because you wanted to win,
and you knew you needed him...

765
01:51:02,222 --> 01:51:04,952
- I didn't have any idea what...
- The fuck you didn't!

766
01:51:06,860 --> 01:51:08,987
The fuck you didn't.

767
01:51:09,596 --> 01:51:13,089
I did everything I could,
and I'm doing everything I can.

768
01:51:13,301 --> 01:51:15,633
Nice to see you.
I'm on my way to Florida.

769
01:51:15,837 --> 01:51:17,395
I'm doing everything I can.

770
01:51:17,605 --> 01:51:20,905
I'm sure. I didn't realize
you'd been out there to see him.

771
01:51:21,110 --> 01:51:24,375
Don't play games with me, Al.
Don't play stupid games.

772
01:51:24,580 --> 01:51:28,244
Nobody gets to go in there.
If I thought I could, I would.

773
01:51:29,119 --> 01:51:31,144
I've sent out hundreds of photographs.

774
01:51:31,354 --> 01:51:35,017
Every relief organization
on the Thai-Kampuchean border...

775
01:51:38,729 --> 01:51:42,529
...has got his picture. If I saw
one glimmer of hope, I'd go today.

776
01:51:43,067 --> 01:51:44,591
Life isn't a '40s movie.

777
01:51:44,802 --> 01:51:48,637
You can't just get on a plane and
make the whole world come out right!

778
01:51:50,242 --> 01:51:53,040
And I can't believe
I'm hearing this from you!

779
01:51:57,850 --> 01:51:59,147
Congrats.

780
01:52:01,220 --> 01:52:03,780
Do you keep in touch
with Dith Pran's family?

781
01:52:03,990 --> 01:52:06,186
Yes. They're living in San Francisco.

782
01:52:06,393 --> 01:52:09,260
How do you respond to accusations
that journalists...

783
01:52:09,463 --> 01:52:11,829
...underestimated the brutality
of the Khmer Rouge...

784
01:52:12,032 --> 01:52:15,764
...and so share responsibility for
what happened in Cambodia afterwards?

785
01:52:16,438 --> 01:52:18,269
We made a mistake.

786
01:52:18,840 --> 01:52:21,434
Maybe we underestimated
the kind of insanity...

787
01:52:21,643 --> 01:52:24,169
...that $ 7 billion worth
of bombing could produce.

788
01:52:24,380 --> 01:52:25,540
That is provocative...

789
01:52:25,748 --> 01:52:29,149
There have been a lot of refugee
stories in Reader's Digest...

790
01:52:29,352 --> 01:52:31,786
...about Cambodia.
Do you believe them?

791
01:52:31,987 --> 01:52:33,546
Don't you believe them?

792
01:52:33,757 --> 01:52:37,625
Maybe in this instance the
Reader's Digest happens to be correct.

793
01:52:37,828 --> 01:52:40,126
Do you apply the same disbelief
to stories...

794
01:52:40,330 --> 01:52:42,822
...that come out of Iran
or Palestine or Chile?

795
01:52:43,034 --> 01:52:45,400
Are refugees your next area
of interest?

796
01:52:45,603 --> 01:52:48,037
Will you be covering the boat people?

797
01:52:48,239 --> 01:52:49,365
No, I will not.

798
01:52:49,574 --> 01:52:51,270
Do you want a cup of tea?

799
01:52:52,244 --> 01:52:55,839
Are you looking around for some kind
of more salable suffering?

800
01:52:58,417 --> 01:53:01,046
I must have sent 500 letters.

801
01:53:06,559 --> 01:53:10,291
I wrote the International Red Cross,
the World Health Organization.

802
01:53:10,498 --> 01:53:13,194
I know you did, Syd.
You told me.

803
01:53:13,701 --> 01:53:15,965
I don't know who I didn't write to.

804
01:53:22,444 --> 01:53:25,106
I never really gave him any choice.

805
01:53:30,553 --> 01:53:33,681
One time we tried to discuss leaving.

806
01:53:42,633 --> 01:53:46,092
I talked to him about it,
but we never really discussed it.

807
01:53:49,407 --> 01:53:52,706
I discussed it with Swain and Rockoff.

808
01:53:56,715 --> 01:53:59,240
But I never discussed it with him.

809
01:54:10,430 --> 01:54:13,366
He stayed because
I wanted him to stay.

810
01:54:19,407 --> 01:54:21,272
And I stayed because...

811
01:58:00,719 --> 01:58:02,585
I'm trapped, Sydney.

812
01:58:02,788 --> 01:58:06,986
I know he suspects me,
and yet he treats me well.

813
01:58:07,626 --> 01:58:11,027
There are many different groups
over here, Sydney.

814
01:58:11,330 --> 01:58:13,424
I must take much care.

815
01:58:13,967 --> 01:58:18,028
Now Angka says we have new enemies.

816
01:58:18,572 --> 01:58:23,476
They say we must regain
our old lands from the Vietnamese.

817
01:58:24,245 --> 01:58:28,147
And now they say we must fight them.

818
01:58:29,952 --> 01:58:34,150
I miss you, my wife, my children.

819
01:58:34,356 --> 01:58:37,814
And my heart hungers for news of you.

820
01:59:01,953 --> 01:59:03,477
New China Radio reports...

821
01:59:03,688 --> 01:59:06,988
...that fighting between Vietnam
and Democratic Kampuchea...

822
01:59:07,193 --> 01:59:09,559
...has broken out
on a number of fronts.

823
01:59:09,829 --> 01:59:12,559
This is in retaliation,
according to the Vietnamese...

824
01:59:12,765 --> 01:59:15,199
...for a number of attacks
on border villages...

825
01:59:18,939 --> 01:59:20,304
Taxi driver, huh?

826
01:59:38,160 --> 01:59:39,991
I think you speak English.

827
01:59:40,462 --> 01:59:41,759
Sit down.

828
01:59:47,971 --> 01:59:50,496
You know, I love this country.

829
01:59:52,309 --> 01:59:55,108
I sacrificed everything for it.

830
01:59:56,581 --> 02:00:00,073
My wife died for the revolution.

831
02:00:01,987 --> 02:00:06,686
But the leaders of Angka
no longer trust the people.

832
02:00:07,626 --> 02:00:11,188
Therefore, I can no longer trust them.

833
02:00:13,032 --> 02:00:15,091
And they don't trust me.

834
02:00:17,604 --> 02:00:18,468
I fear...

835
02:00:19,873 --> 02:00:22,206
...really fear for the future.

836
02:00:26,614 --> 02:00:30,107
I think you love my son.

837
02:00:33,221 --> 02:00:34,483
For his sake...

838
02:00:35,557 --> 02:00:36,956
...look after him.

839
02:00:41,597 --> 02:00:44,191
The fighting is close by, Sydney.

840
02:00:44,400 --> 02:00:46,868
If the Vietnamese get here...

841
02:00:47,069 --> 02:00:49,231
...Angka will destroy everything...

842
02:00:51,375 --> 02:00:52,933
...and the Vietnamese,
they will find only ashes.

843
02:04:02,286 --> 02:04:05,722
I must try to stop the killing.
Good luck.

844
02:13:25,143 --> 02:13:27,043
Yeah, I'll be right there, Brian.

845
02:13:29,982 --> 02:13:33,941
Ann, get me 415-555-6421.

846
02:13:34,153 --> 02:13:35,848
Abe, I've got some great news!

847
02:13:49,070 --> 02:13:52,130
Twenty minutes ago, I get
a phone call from Paris.

848
02:13:52,340 --> 02:13:55,241
I get Andreas Freund.
He talked to Henry.

849
02:13:55,443 --> 02:13:57,537
He told him how to get in touch
with me.

850
02:13:57,746 --> 02:14:00,613
Freund says, "I have got
some great news for you."

851
02:14:00,816 --> 02:14:03,444
- San Francisco's on the line.
- "It's about Pran!"

852
02:14:03,819 --> 02:14:05,515
Is your mother there?

853
02:14:08,124 --> 02:14:09,284
When?

854
02:14:11,694 --> 02:14:14,357
All right,
I want you to get this down.

855
02:14:15,199 --> 02:14:17,861
No, write it down. Write it down.

856
02:14:19,403 --> 02:14:21,530
I've got a message from your dad!

857
02:15:34,486 --> 02:15:35,680
How you been?

858
02:15:48,769 --> 02:15:49,793
Do you forgive me?

859
02:15:50,504 --> 02:15:53,098
Nothing to forgive, Sydney.
Nothing.

